his theory provides useful tools for studying large classes of initial-boundary value evolution problems, the main aim being to obtain a constructive approximation to the associated positive C0-semigroups by means of iterates of suitable positive approximating operators. As a consequence, a qualitative analysis of the solutions to the evolution problems can be efficiently developed. The book is mainly addressed to research mathematicians interested in modern approximation theory by positive linear operators and/or in the theory of positive C0-semigroups of operators and evolution equations. It could also serve as a textbook for a graduate level course.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBoundary value problems. 0aDifferential operators. 0aMarkov operators. 0aSemigroups. 4aMarkov Semigruppen. 4aPositive Approximationsprozesse. 7aMATHEMATICS / Functional Analysis.2bisacsh1 aCappelletti, Mirella, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLeonessa, Vita, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRasa, Ioan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Studies in Mathematics eBook-Packagez978311049493808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics, Physics 2014z9783110370355oZDB-23-DEM0 cEPUBz97831103864170 cprintz978311037274840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311036697640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110366976423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110366976.jpg  a978-3-11-049493-8  DG Studies in Mathematics eBook-Package  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Pl